“Chronosync: A Culinary Time Weaver” – A wearable device, resembling a minimalist wrist cuff, that subtly manipulates a diner’s perception of time during a meal. It utilizes a combination of micro-vibrations, targeted aroma diffusion (think pre-programmed ‘nostalgia’ scents – freshly baked bread, rain on pavement), temperature gradients applied to the skin via thermoelectric elements, and precisely calibrated binaural beats delivered through bone conduction. The device learns the diner’s physiological responses – heart rate, pupil dilation, neural activity – to dynamically adjust the sensory stimuli, creating the illusion of a lengthened or shortened meal experience. Imagine savoring every bite of a rich chocolate dessert, experiencing it as if it lasted twice as long, or speeding through a bland appetizer with blissful acceleration! It’s like having a personal time chef!